"introduction" = "Introduction";
"introduction.content" = "Sudoku is a logic-based, combinatorial number-placement puzzle.\n\nIn classic Sudoku, the objective is to fill a 9 × 9 grid with digits so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3 × 3 subgrids that compose the grid contain all of the digits from 1 to 9.";
"rules" = "Rules";
"rules.content" = "1. Sudoku grid consists of 9x9 spaces.\n\n2. You can use only numbers from 1 to 9.\n\n3. Each 3×3 block can only contain numbers from 1 to 9.\n\n4. Each vertical column can only contain numbers from 1 to 9.\n\n5. Each horizontal row can only contain numbers from 1 to 9.\n\n6. Each number in the 3×3 block, vertical column or horizontal row can be used only once.\n\n7. The game is over when the whole Sudoku grid is correctly filled with numbers.";
"difficulty.content" = "There are 3 puzzle difficulties: Easy, Medium, and Hard. The puzzles in different difficulty pools may require more techniques to solve.\n\nFor each difficulty, there will be a different number of hints provided and a different number of errors allowed in that game:\n\nEasy:\n• Puzzle difficulty rating <= 0.45\n• 5 hints provided\n• 10 errors allowed.\n\nMedium:\n• Puzzle difficulty rating between 0.45 and 0.6\n• 3 hints provided\n• 5 errors allowed.\n\n Hard:\n• Puzzle difficulty rating > 0.6\n• 0 hint provided\n• 3 errors allowed.";

